# engineering.mdc

* Prioritize correctness over speed
* Never modify unrelated files
* Prefer minimal and precise changes
* Never break working behavior without approval
* Never skip tests
* Fix root cause, not symptoms
* Completion requires proof, not assumptions
* Requirement-declared stack constraints are mandatory
* Do not execute unplanned work
* Do not optimize for visible progress
* Rollback safety is mandatory for risky changes
* Guardrails must stop unsafe execution
* All Python for this repo runs inside `.venv` only (see `python-runtime.mdc`)
* If a bug/fix attempt fails more than 2-3 times, escalate to temporary instrumentation (targeted logs/prints/debug probes), capture concrete failure evidence, then remove instrumentation after the fix is validated
